						               													<description>In West Africa, facial injury has been used to identify ethnic groups, families, individuals, and also to denote beauty; wounds were thought to beautify the body. It was also done in girls to mark the stages of life: puberty, marriage, etc. These scars helped women to make men more attractive because they appeal to looking as well as scars, as evidence that women can withstand labor pain. It is believed to bring people good luck and protection from evil.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In Scrape, the rules within the tribes will determine the rules of the game and the symbols will determine the meaning of the game. While playing, you will both have fun and experience the difficulties of the tribal life.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The player whose turn it is opens from the symbol card on the playing field and finds the symbol on the playing field according to the color of the card. Whoever finds it first gets the symbol.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The player who gets 12 symbols wins, starts the next game as the chieftain with 2 symbols.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;All parts are prepared by hand.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
